        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Add the various Golem mobs in the Plane of Fear to the un-tapable list as well as the fright(s?) and terror.  We all tried a few times, highest level was 58 SK and 55 Necro that tried last night.  Most of the other mobs in Fear that we fought (Nightmares, Frogs, Amys, Glare Lords and such) took life tap quite well and it is an effective way of combating.  Something I have found out though, if our lifetap resists in the "uber" encounters, so does most other casters spells...  The uber encounters seem to be most effective when you can throw a bunch of tanks at them with plenty of healing/buffing and the mana/support personell to back em up.  Some mobs can be more effectively casted upon once they are debuffed (ie cold and fire based spells work pretty well or resist less when debuffed in that fashion) but a lot of the resists depend on the level of the mob and it's resists level.</P><P>By the way, as an Iksar necro I do not find that I have to cast taps/bod on mobs to stay alive...  As long as I have regrowth/regen I can keep my health up just fine without having to drop lich.  I think all you darkies just need to start over...   =p  Seriously though, if I don't have to waste my mana on resisted taps and such it gives me more for casting spells that do work (acid blast works, almost completely unresisted, on alot of "uber" mobs suprisingly!) as well as having more mana for dumping, spot healing, DMF, and the other various spells that can work on some mobs (ie heat or cold or whatever the mob is debuffed/less resistant of).</P><P>Ssauron<BR>~Level 52 Necromancer<BR>~Cabilis, Kunark<BR>~Rodcet Nife<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
