        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">About the DoT bug:<BR>To my understanding it cannot be fixed! But it does not occur very often.</P><P>If a mob dies to unknown damage then the corpse will go poof. When you cast a DoT on a mob then the DoT-damage will be asigned to your name. Now when someone wipes the hatelist and the mob dies to 'your' DoT then it does not remember who did the damage and goes poof. It is that simple and it cannot be fixed of course. It does not happen that often since chances are slim that your FD clears aggro OR someone wipes memory AND your DoT kills the mob at the same time.<BR>Just a very very rare coincidence these days. </P><P><BR><img src="http://home.nexgo.de/neric/Data/Neric_sig.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
